(2) If during a preliminary inquiry held under the Criminal Procedure Code the court considers that— (a) having regard to all the circumstances of the case it is desirable in the interests of justice that the accused should be represented by a practitioner at that inquiry; and (b) the accused has insufficient means to enable him to engage a practitioner to represent him; the court shall recommend to the Director that the accused be granted legal aid . [ Cap. 88 ]
